  "Correct positioning: independent research drafts, protocol proposals, and an open specification experiment.": "Boemo jo bo tototo: disekao tsa patlisiso tse di ikemetseng ka bolona, ditshitshinyo tsa porotokole, le teko ya ditlhalosetso tse di bulegileng.",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Belgium (BE) now maps to Dutch instead of French — Flemish speakers are the country’s majority (~60%) over Walloon French speakers (~40%).": "Go siamisitswe maemo a pele: Belgium (BE) jaanong e supa Dutch go na le Sefora — babui ba Seflemishe ke bontsi jwa naga (~60%) go feta babui ba Sefora ba Walloon (~40%).",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Kazakhstan (KZ) now maps to Kazakh instead of Russian, now that a Kazakh translation exists — the same kind of fix as the earlier Belgium correction.": "Go siamisitswe maemo a pele: Kazakhstan (KZ) jaanong e supa Sekazakh go na le Serashea, ka jaanong go na le thanolo ya Sekazakh — mofuta o o tshwanang wa tokafatso jaaka ya Belgium pele.",
  "Could AI Be Conscious?": "Could AI Be Conscious?",
  "Crawler access rules": "Melawana ya phitlhelelo ya di-crawler",
  "Crawler simulator": "Sedirisiwa sa go Tshwantshetsa Di-crawler",
  "Currency": "Madi",
  "Custom tier": "Maemo a o a Itlhamang",
  "Daily Nous reports on a retracted Journal of Medical Ethics submission containing multiple fabricated, AI-hallucinated references — complete with fake university affiliations and defunct email addresses — that the author reportedly left uncorrected even after being given a chance to fix proofs. The piece contrasts this with Bioethics, whose automated reference-checking would have caught the problem, and argues the real bottleneck isn't detection technology (one commenter's script flagged the fake citations in under a minute) but unpaid reviewer labor and publishing incentives that reward throughput over scrutiny.": "Daily Nous e bega ka lokwalo lo lo neng lo phasaladitswe kwa Journal of Medical Ethics lo bo lo gogwa gape, lo lo neng lo na le ditsopolo tse dintsi tse di iponetsweng, tse di dirilweng ke AI ka phoso (AI-hallucinated), tse di feletseng ka digolaganyo tsa dikolo tsa boithuto tse di sa gôname le diaterese tsa email tse di sa dirisiweng — tse mokwadi a neng a sa di siamisa le fa a ne a filwe sebaka sa go siamisa dikakanyo pele di gatisiwa. Sengwalo se se bapisa se le Bioethics, e leng khampani e tlhotlhomiso ya yona ya ditsopolo e e itiragalelang e neng e tla bo e bonye bothata, mme se bua gore bothata jo bo tototo ga se thekenoloji ya go bona (khoutu ya monni-mongwe e ne ya supa ditsopolo tsa maaka mo motsotswaneng o mongwe fela), mme ke tiro e e sa duelweng ya baseki le dikgothaletso tsa go gatisa tse di duelang bontsi go na le kelotlhoko.",
  "Data free-riding vs. trillion-dollar AI valuations": "Go dirisa data ka mahala kgatlhanong le ditekanyo tsa AI tsa dimilionemilione tsa bodola",
  "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI": "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI",
  "Demis Hassabis proposed a FINRA-style regulator for frontier model releases: labs would submit models for review up to 30 days before deployment, voluntary at first, with a path toward mandatory compliance in the US market.": "Demis Hassabis o tshitshintse molaodi wa mofuta wa FINRA bakeng sa tlhagiso ya dimodele tse di kwa pele: ditlelabo di ka romela dimodele go sekasekiwa mo malatsing a ka nnang 30 pele ga di dirisiwa, e le boithaopo pele, ka tsela e e yang go go patelelwa mo mmarakeng wa US.",
  "Denied": "Go Ganwe",
  "Deployable policy starter template": "Sesupo sa go Simolola sa Pholisi se se ka Dirisiwang Ka Bonako",
  "Deployable policy starter template at /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — a minimal static site with the full machine-readable layer, ready for Cloudflare Pages or any static host.": "Sesupo sa go simolola sa pholisi se se ka dirisiwang ka bonako se mo /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — lefelo le lennye la enthanete le le nang le maleba a a balwang ke metšhini ka botlalo, le siametse Cloudflare Pages kgotsa lefelo lepe fela le le nnang jalo.",
  "Deploying machine-readable policies on your site": "Go tsenya dipholisi tse di balwang ke metšhini mo lefelong la gago",
  "Disclaimer": "Kitsiso ya Boikarabelo",
  "Distinct from human UI, SEO, or plain APIs, the AI Ingestion & Capability Layer gives websites a machine-facing architecture: a Manifest Layer (entry points like /llms.txt and /ai/manifest.json), a Corpus Layer (machine-readable knowledge), a Capability Layer (agent-callable tools), and a Governance Layer (provenance, licensing, versioning). Static-first, upgradeable toward APIs and MCP. Note: in this paper AICL names the ingestion architecture; on this site's protocol pages AICL refers to the AI Content Licensing Layer.": "Ka go farologana le UI ya batho, SEO, kgotsa di-API tse di tlwaelesegileng, AI Ingestion & Capability Layer e naya mafelo a enthanete thulaganyo e e lebaganeng le metšhini: Maleba a Manifest (dintlha tsa go tsena tse di jaaka /llms.txt le /ai/manifest.json), Maleba a Corpus (kitso e e balwang ke metšhini), Maleba a Capability (didirisiwa tse di ka bidiwang ke baemedi), le Maleba a Governance (motswedi, kabo ya dilaesense, ditokololo). E simolola e le e e sa fetogeng (static), e kgona go godisiwa go ya go di-API le MCP. Kgopotso: mo pampiring eno AICL e supa thulaganyo ya go amogela; mo ditsebeng tsa porotokole tsa lefelo leno AICL e kaya Maleba a Kabo ya Dilaesense tsa Diteng tsa AI.",
  "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm": "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm",
  "Docs": "Dikwalo",
  "Docs / Examples": "Dikwalo / Dikao",
  "Document library": "Laeborari ya Dikwalo",
