  "Verified dataset markets and collective licensing": "Mebaraka ya Disete tsa Data tse di Netefaditsweng le Kabo ya Dilaesense ya Setlhopha",
  "Verified in both LTR and RTL contexts: the panel mirrors correctly for Arabic and Persian without any special-casing, using logical CSS positioning.": "E netefaditswe mo maemong a LTR le a RTL: poranele e ipona sentle bakeng sa Searabia le Sepersi kwa ntle ga go rulaganngwa ka thoko, ka go dirisa maemo a logical CSS.",
  "Verify": "Netefatsa",
  "Version history of this site and its protocol drafts.": "Hisitori ya Ditokololo ya Lefelo Leno le Disekao tsa Yona tsa Porotokole.",
  "Version history of this site and its protocol drafts. Breaking spec changes are recorded here.": "Hisitori ya ditokololo ya lefelo leno le disekao tsa yona tsa porotokole. Diphetogo tse dikgolo tsa ditlhalosetso di kwadilwe fano.",
  "Versioned specifications, JSON Schemas, and the policy files actually deployed on this site. Every file can be downloaded, validated, and cited directly.": "Ditlhalosetso tse di nang le ditokololo, Disekema tsa JSON, le difaele tsa pholisi tse di tsentsweng tota mo lefelong leno. Faele nngwe le nngwe e ka kokotelwa, ya netefadiwa, mme ya tsopolwa ka tlhamalalo.",
  "Versioning": "Go Dira Ditokololo",
  "Versions": "Ditokololo",
  "Video and audio companions to the protocols and papers — the AI rights layer, watchable and listenable.": "Dividio le medumo e e tsamayang le diporotokole le dipampiri — maleba a ditshwanelo tsa AI, a a ka lebelelwang le go reetswa.",
  "Videos": "Dividio",
  "Want to generate your own policy file?": "A o batla go dira faele ya gago ya pholisi?",
  "Web fonts are loaded from Google Fonts, which receives standard font requests from your browser. No other third-party scripts are used.": "Difonto tsa enthanete di laisiwa go tswa kwa Google Fonts, e e amogelang dikopo tsa tlwaelo tsa fonto go tswa mo praosareng ya gago. Ga go dikhoutu dingwe tsa batho ba bangwe tse di dirisiwang.",
  "What AI systems may do with content: read, summarize, transform, retrieve, train, commercialize, redistribute. The AICR ruleset and the AICL licensing layer make these rights declarable and transactable.": "Se ditsamaiso tsa AI di ka se dirang ka diteng: go bala, go kgutlhufatsa, go fetola, go tsaya, go ithuta, go dira ka kgwebo, go aba. Melawana ya AICR le maleba a kabo ya dilaesense a AICL di dira gore ditshwanelo tseno di kgone go tsibosiwa le go dirisiwa mo dithekesekeng.",
  "What a server can return when an AI crawler requests licensed content without a license token — a machine-actionable quote instead of a dead end.": "Se seabi (server) se ka se busang fa crawler ya AI e kopa diteng tse di nang le laesense kwa ntle ga tokene ya laesense — tekanyo ya theko e e ka diragadiwang ke metšhini go na le tsela e e sa gorogeng gope.",
  "What this site is": "Se Lefelo Leno e leng Sona",
  "What this site is not": "Se Lefelo Leno e leng Sona Seng",
  "When The Machines Deserve Our Consideration": "When The Machines Deserve Our Consideration",
  "Whether AI may learn, to what depth, for which purposes, and under what obligations. Being read is not being learned from; \"not prohibited\" is not \"learnable\". AIRS and AILP turn learning permission into a graduated, machine-readable spectrum.": "A AI e ka ithuta, ka boteng bofe, bakeng sa merero efe, le ka fa maikarabelong afe. Go balwa ga se go ithutwa ka gone; \"go sa thibelwa\" ga se \"go ithutwang\". AIRS le AILP di fetola tetlelelo ya go ithuta go nna sekala se se katlegang, se se balwang ke metšhini.",
  "Whitepapers": "Dipampiri tse Tshweu",
  "Whitepapers & Docs": "Dipampiri tse Tshweu le Dikwalo",
  "Whitepapers remain English-first by design; machine-readable files stay language-neutral.": "Dipampiri tse tshweu di sala e le Sekgowa pele ka boomo; difaele tse di balwang ke metšhini di sala di sa tseye letlhakore la teme.",
  "Who is behind it": "Ke Mang yo o Emeng Kwa Morago ga Yona",
  "Why AI Needs Minimum Ethical Protections": "Why AI Needs Minimum Ethical Protections",
  "Why AI might not gain moral standing: Lessons from animal ethics": "Why AI might not gain moral standing: Lessons from animal ethics",
  "Why a single allow/deny bit cannot govern AI-era content use — and what a rights layer looks like instead.": "Ke ka lebaka la eng bit e le nngwe ya dumela/gana e sa kgone go laola tiriso ya diteng mo nakong ya AI — le gore maleba a ditshwanelo a lebega jang go na le yona.",
  "Why undefined openness gets cleaned out of training pipelines": "Ke ka lebaka la eng bobulegi jo bo sa tlhalosiwang bo tlosiwa mo dithulaganyong tsa thupelo",
  "Wilks, Ladak, and Loughnan (University of Edinburgh) argue that philosophical debate over AI consciousness overlooks psychological research on animal ethics — the same cognitive and social biases that limit moral consideration for animals will likely limit it for AI too, regardless of whether AI ever becomes conscious.": "Wilks, Ladak, le Loughnan (University of Edinburgh) ba bua gore kganetsanyo ya filosofi ka ga boitemogelo jwa AI e itlhokomolosa patlisiso ya kelotlhoko ka boitshwaro jwa diphologolo — dikgethololo tse di tshwanang tsa kelotlhoko le tsa loago tse di fokotsang kelotlhoko ya boitshwaro bakeng sa diphologolo di tla nna tsa fokotsa le yona bakeng sa AI, go sa kgathalesege gore a AI e tla kile ya itemogela kgotsa nnyaya.",
  "You are leaving AGIRight.org": "O tswa mo AGIRight.org",
